title: Carnival Queen (film)
text: Carnival Queen is a 1937 American <a href="crime%20film">crime film</a> directed by <a href="Nate%20Watt">Nate Watt</a> and written by James Mulhauser and Harold Buckley. The film stars <a href="Robert%20Wilcox%20%28actor%29">Robert Wilcox</a>, <a href="Dorothea%20Kent">Dorothea Kent</a>, <a href="Hobart%20Cavanaugh">Hobart Cavanaugh</a>, <a href="G.%20Pat%20Collins">G. Pat Collins</a>, Harry Tyler, <a href="Ernest%20Cossart">Ernest Cossart</a>, David Oliver, Billy Wayne, <a href="Jonathan%20Hale">Jonathan Hale</a> and Raymond Brown. It was released on October 3, 1937, by <a href="Universal%20Pictures">Universal Pictures</a>.
